# Image tiling

**Tiling** an image is **cutting** it **down into smaller image pieces** called tiles (as an example a 1024 x 1024 image can be cut into four 512 x 512 tiles, see below). 

Tiles can be overlapping (this can improve model prediction at tile edge).

**Tiling is of use**:
<br>
* When the **deep learning model requires an input image with a given size that differs from that of the original input image**.
<br> 
* To **prevent the system from running out of memory**. Training a deep learning model can be very memory demanding.
